Vice President Mike Pence delivers a commencement speech to the United States Naval Academy Class of 2017. He congratulates the new officers and offers the congratulations of President Donald Trump. Pence highlights the importance of their service to the country and acknowledges the sacrifices made by those who have gone before them. He emphasizes the qualities of leadership and character that they should strive for, including humility, orientation to authority, and self-control. Pence also reassures the new officers that President Trump is committed to rebuilding and supporting the military. He urges them to write their own heroic stories of service and selflessness and concludes by encouraging them to have faith in themselves and in their country.